post_text:
This afternoon area superintendents gathered to develop protocols for the current Coronavirus situation.

Here are highlights of the agreement;
Suspend all large, indoor gatherings and field trips between March 16th and April 5th and to then reassess the next steps at that time,

Districts will provide deep cleaning of buildings and facilities;

Any possible closing of schools would be announced jointly and be made in consultation with a county or state health official;

Provide alternative options to students to address academic work in the event of the closure of school for multiple days;

Agreement to partner with local public health offices as applicable (Galion City Health Department and Crawford County Public Health) regarding strategic steps and recommendations for specific action;

Districts will develop regular communication protocols to maintain communications with students, parents, and community members.

For more information,
COVID-19 Updates and Press Releases can be found on our website at https://www.galionschools.org/departments/clinic-resources/influenzacoronavirus

